262
00:16:25,433 --> 00:16:27,633
I want you to try them.

263
00:16:27,767 --> 00:16:29,800
Okay, Bobby, wait a minute.
I'll just order.

264
00:16:29,933 --> 00:16:31,733
Okay, it's up to you.

265
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:38,600
Madam, you know,
instead of getting annoyed,

266
00:16:38,733 --> 00:16:41,433
let's just go shopping.

267
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:43,533
You can't make her leave.

268
00:16:43,667 --> 00:16:46,500
Ma'am Faye asked her to stay.

269
00:16:46,633 --> 00:16:47,633
It's up to you,

270
00:16:47,767 --> 00:16:49,800
if Ma'am Faye finds out
that you made her leave.

271
00:16:49,933 --> 00:16:51,367
She'll be mad at you.

272
00:16:52,467 --> 00:16:55,433
I know, but someone
has to do it.

273
00:17:02,767 --> 00:17:03,533
Cheka?

274
00:17:03,667 --> 00:17:04,667
Yes?

275
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:07,333
I have something petty in mind.

276
00:17:07,467 --> 00:17:10,267
Madam, calm down.

277
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:13,167
Would you like me to order you
a watermelon shake?

278
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:19,167
Okay, order a watermelon shake,
but it's not for me.

279
00:17:19,333 --> 00:17:21,400
For whom?

280
00:17:21,533 --> 00:17:27,900
I remember I have a new friend
who's very fond of Bobby.

281
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:59,600
Bro, how are you?
Long time no see.

282
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:01,267
That's from boss.

283
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:08,100
The governor is still nice.

284
00:18:08,233 --> 00:18:10,000
That's two batches of fifty.

285
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:14,633
But he said...

286
00:18:17,133 --> 00:18:19,367
when you escape from here,

287
00:18:19,500 --> 00:18:21,833
you have to work for him.

288
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:26,400
No problem,
I'll take care of it.

289
00:18:26,533 --> 00:18:29,033
I just have one thing
to cross off my list...

290
00:18:30,633 --> 00:18:31,700
It's Conde.

291
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:52,533
Bobby!

292
00:19:06,933 --> 00:19:08,533
Bobby, you're so petty!

293
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:10,133
Just because you lost the race,

294
00:19:10,267 --> 00:19:11,667
you messed up my things
to get back at me.

295
00:19:14,667 --> 00:19:16,933
What are you saying?
I didn't do that.

296
00:19:17,067 --> 00:19:18,400
What? You're denying it?

297
00:19:18,533 --> 00:19:20,033
Who's going to throw a shake
in my bag?

298
00:19:20,167 --> 00:19:21,133
Isn't it just you?

299
00:19:21,267 --> 00:19:23,067
Charlie, please, not now.

300
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,400
There are so many people
who can buy a shake.

301
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,267
You just want drama.

302
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:31,167
I'm still talking to you.

303
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:32,567
Madam...

304
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:36,167
you just ordered a catfight,
but a war came.

305
00:19:37,933 --> 00:19:42,033
Well, this is much better
than that swimming race.

306
00:19:42,167 --> 00:19:44,900
Do you think I'll accept
that you just threw it at me?

307
00:19:49,433 --> 00:19:51,033
Madam...

308
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:54,033
There you go, I threw it!

309
00:19:54,167 --> 00:19:55,700
What happened here?

310
00:19:56,667 --> 00:19:58,633
Bobby, you started this,
didn't you?

311
00:19:58,767 --> 00:20:00,533
I'm not the one
who's causing trouble.

312
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:03,067
Mommy, Bobby didn't start it.
It's her!

313
00:20:03,233 --> 00:20:04,000
What?

314
00:20:04,133 --> 00:20:05,000
Faye...

315
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:10,200
can you stop defending
this girl?

316
00:20:10,333 --> 00:20:13,567
And please, stop hanging out
with her

317
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:17,200
because she'll only teach you
violence.

318
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:20,033
And you, next time,

319
00:20:20,167 --> 00:20:24,767
don't force yourself into things
that aren't for you.

320
00:20:26,567 --> 00:20:27,700
Noted.

321
00:20:27,833 --> 00:20:28,967
Excuse me, Faye.

322
00:20:29,100 --> 00:20:30,833
- I'll go ahead.
- Bobby, I'll walk you out.

323
00:20:37,867 --> 00:20:40,233
Madam, next time,

324
00:20:40,367 --> 00:20:42,467
don't order me to do things
like that.

325
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:44,200
What if Charlie caught me

326
00:20:44,333 --> 00:20:46,200
who threw the watermelon shake
in her bag?

327
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:48,967
If that's the case,
I'd be in the body bag.

328
00:20:49,100 --> 00:20:52,200
Besides, Madam,
being petty doesn't suit you.

329
00:20:53,433 --> 00:20:55,033
Petty has its rewards.

330
00:20:56,133 --> 00:21:00,100
And I think I know why Bobby
came into our lives.

331
00:21:01,267 --> 00:21:02,533
Why, Madam?

332
00:21:04,467 --> 00:21:05,800
You know,

333
00:21:05,933 --> 00:21:09,533
there's a lot I didn't do
to Bobby's mother.

334
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:13,167
I didn't slap her,
I didn't pull her hair,

335
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:14,967
I didn't embarrass her.

336
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:21,733
But it feels really good
knowing that I can do all that

337
00:21:21,867 --> 00:21:23,133
to her daughter.

338
00:21:34,533 --> 00:21:35,600
I'll go to you.

339
00:21:36,967 --> 00:21:38,267
Let's see each other tomorrow.

340
00:21:40,533 --> 00:21:42,367
Yes, don't worry.
I still have some.

341
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:03,267
Mando?

342
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:05,600
Sir...

343
00:22:08,733 --> 00:22:10,033
What's this?

344
00:22:11,733 --> 00:22:13,900
Look at what's under the bread,
Sir.

345
00:22:18,267 --> 00:22:19,800
This is okay.

346
00:22:19,933 --> 00:22:21,333
How much is this?

347
00:22:21,467 --> 00:22:22,867
Fifty thousand, Sir.

348
00:22:24,233 --> 00:22:25,600
This isn't enough.

349
00:22:25,733 --> 00:22:29,533
The other half is still
on the other bread, Sir.

350
00:22:29,667 --> 00:22:30,633
Is that so?

351
00:22:30,767 --> 00:22:32,033
Very good.

352
00:22:33,200 --> 00:22:34,567
And because of that,

353
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:38,833
I'll give you everything
you need for your move.

354
00:22:38,967 --> 00:22:39,800
Nice.

355
00:22:41,733 --> 00:22:43,000
Thank you, Sir.

356
00:22:48,967 --> 00:22:49,967
Okay, okay.

357
00:22:52,867 --> 00:22:53,900
Bok, Bok!

358
00:22:54,033 --> 00:22:55,367
You're just here.

359
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:57,167
- Oh, why?
- I've been looking for you.

360
00:22:57,300 --> 00:22:58,433
What do you need?

361
00:22:58,567 --> 00:23:01,067
Haven't you seen it yet?
Look at this!

362
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:03,367
There, look at Faye's
social media account.

363
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:06,100
There are so many people
commenting about Bobby.

364
00:23:06,233 --> 00:23:07,167
There...

365
00:23:07,300 --> 00:23:10,767
Men are asking what Bobby's
social media is?

366
00:23:10,900 --> 00:23:12,000
Where is she from?

367
00:23:12,133 --> 00:23:12,900
How old is she?

368
00:23:13,033 --> 00:23:14,667
Here are some samples.

369
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:16,600
Kevin Debela.

370
00:23:16,733 --> 00:23:20,067
"Ma'am Bobby is beautiful
and sexy."

371
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,933
Obet Guiller.

372
00:23:22,100 --> 00:23:24,967
"What's Ma'am Bobby's ASL?"

373
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:26,533
Mark Caba.

374
00:23:27,633 --> 00:23:29,733
"Our family is not a family
of ghosts.

375
00:23:29,867 --> 00:23:34,200
But Ma'am Bobby is a beast
with her beauty."

376
00:23:34,333 --> 00:23:35,233
You see?

377
00:23:35,367 --> 00:23:37,333
Look at those people commenting.

378
00:23:37,467 --> 00:23:39,200
They look like scammers.

379
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:43,567
Well, if one of those guys
courts Bobby, you're dead.

380
00:23:44,733 --> 00:23:46,767
Especially this one,
I saw a handsome guy earlier.

381
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:47,767
There.

382
00:23:48,700 --> 00:23:50,433
He looks like Joross Gamboa.

383
00:23:50,567 --> 00:23:52,433
That one has a strong
sex appeal.

384
00:23:52,567 --> 00:23:55,833
I'm sure Bobby will not
answer any of them,

385
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,400
not even one.

386
00:23:57,533 --> 00:23:59,367
Well, they don't know Bobby.

387
00:23:59,500 --> 00:24:03,367
Besides, Bobby doesn't fall
for just anyone.

388
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:07,000
Bok, I know someone.

389
00:24:07,133 --> 00:24:10,267
I'm sure Bobby won't answer
that one.

390
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:11,300
Who?

391
00:24:11,433 --> 00:24:14,000
The one who isn't courting her.

392
00:24:16,667 --> 00:24:18,700
Okay, Bok. I'll go ahead, okay?

393
00:24:18,833 --> 00:24:20,067
I'll just fix this.

394
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:21,867
I'll post a comment here.

395
00:24:30,033 --> 00:24:30,800
Where's grandmother?

396
00:24:32,167 --> 00:24:33,100
At home.

397
00:24:33,233 --> 00:24:35,067
She is not feeling well
right now.

398
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:38,733
But if you find out
that she's not coming.

399
00:24:38,867 --> 00:24:41,033
You might not want
to treat us anymore.

400
00:24:41,167 --> 00:24:44,267
Besides, Bobby, there's
a reason to celebrate, right?

401
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:45,333
What?

402
00:24:45,467 --> 00:24:47,700
What happened earlier
at the swimming pool.

403
00:24:47,833 --> 00:24:49,500
But didn't I lose?

404
00:24:49,633 --> 00:24:52,133
Girl, you won there.

405
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:54,833
Look at Faye's post.

406
00:24:54,967 --> 00:24:56,533
Let's read the comments section.

407
00:24:56,667 --> 00:24:59,933
Girl, there are a lot of people
who want to meet you, right?

408
00:25:00,067 --> 00:25:02,700
Yes, and they're asking
if you have a boyfriend,

409
00:25:02,867 --> 00:25:05,933
especially your social media
accounts, right?

410
00:25:06,067 --> 00:25:07,100
Gosh!

411
00:25:07,233 --> 00:25:09,700
Abdul, I don't have time
for that stuff, please.

412
00:25:09,833 --> 00:25:11,633
Bobby, we know.

413
00:25:11,767 --> 00:25:13,767
That's why Mar and I came up
with a plan.

414
00:25:14,900 --> 00:25:18,833
What if we pretend to be Bobby?

415
00:25:18,967 --> 00:25:20,200
So they will court us!

416
00:25:20,333 --> 00:25:21,533
Yes!

417
00:25:21,667 --> 00:25:23,800
That's amazing!

418
00:25:23,933 --> 00:25:25,667
What you're doing is illegal!

419
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:26,700
That's catfishing.

420
00:25:26,833 --> 00:25:28,133
Bobby, come on...

421
00:25:28,267 --> 00:25:29,333
Wait.

422
00:25:29,467 --> 00:25:31,667
Don't you want to be courted?

423
00:25:31,800 --> 00:25:32,867
Who knows,

424
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:34,833
you'll stumble upon someone
in that comment section.

425
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,867
Someone else will be interested
in you.

426
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:39,067
It's not that she doesn't
want to be courted,

427
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:41,400
she already likes someone.

428
00:25:41,533 --> 00:25:43,933
None other than...

429
00:25:44,067 --> 00:25:44,933
Bobby!

430
00:25:51,800 --> 00:25:56,000
Bobby mentioned to me
that you have a boyfriend.

431
00:25:56,133 --> 00:25:57,433
That's not true, right?

432
00:25:57,567 --> 00:25:59,300
You don't have a boyfriend,
right?

433
00:25:59,433 --> 00:26:01,833
Yes, Doc Cecilia does have
a boyfriend.

434
00:26:01,967 --> 00:26:02,500
Me.

435
00:26:02,633 --> 00:26:03,900
Boss Tonyo, good evening.

436
00:26:04,033 --> 00:26:06,833
I saw your girlfriend here,
almost naked.

437
00:26:06,967 --> 00:26:08,233
If you want,
after your hot shower,

438
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,433
I'll give you a massage.

439
00:26:09,567 --> 00:26:10,733
I give a good massage.

440
00:26:10,867 --> 00:26:13,833
Those Calabari inmates who were
being moved to a new facility

441
00:26:13,967 --> 00:26:14,967
escaped.

442
00:26:15,100 --> 00:26:18,833
I heard one of those inmates
is Mandong Warak.

443
00:26:18,967 --> 00:26:21,467
He's very notorious
for killing policemen.

444
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:23,867
Good luck to Garcia
if he escaped.

445
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,333
He might kill him next.

446
00:26:28,167 --> 00:26:29,433
Are you looking for me?
